article.headline: Belmont 91, Jacksonville 78
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- Justin Hare came off the bench to score 22 points to lead Belmont to a 91-78 win over Jacksonville Monday. Hare scored 15 points in the second half when Belmont outscored Jacksonville 53-32 after the Dolphins held an 8-point lead (46-38) at halftime. The Bruins (6-7, 4-2 in A-Sun play) hit a blistering 68 percent from the floor in the final 20 minutes, connecting on 17 of 25 shots. They finished at 56 percent (30 of 54) for the game. Hare's jump shot at the 16:30 mark of the second half ignited a 15-1 spurt over a five minute span when the Bruins turned a 53-45 deficit into a 60-54 advantage. Hare, freshman of the year in the Atlantic Sun Conference a year ago, finished the run with a 3-point basket to give the visitors a six-point lead. Jacksonville (1-12, 1-5) reduced the visitors' lead to 62-61 midway in the second half, but Belmont reeled off 12 consecutive points to open a 13-point lead with just under seven minutes left and led by at least 10 points the rest of the game. The Dolphins got 18 points from Antonio Cool who scored in double figures for the eighth consecutive game.
